{"questionId":"27747586","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>On the same day, the height of water at the second island, Rockall, is modelled by the function&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>b</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>d</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is the number of hours after midnight, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>The first low tide occurs at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>02</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>41</mn></math> when the height of the water is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>The first high tide occurs at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>09</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>02</mn></math> when the height of the water is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>74</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the rate of change of the height of the water when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>13</mn></math>, giving your answer in metres per hour.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>H</mi><mo>'</mo><mfenced><mn>13</mn></mfenced></math> is required&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>650622</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>651</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mo>/</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">h</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27747586","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ1.8c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the rate of change of the height of the water when t=13, giving your answer in metres per hour.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.1—Introduction of differential calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product and quotient rules"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
